-- Lira Weakens Second Day, Heads for Lowest Level in Two Weeks
-- B y   S e l c u k   G o k o l u k
-- 2012-04-09T06:37:49Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-09/lira-weakens-second-day-heads-for-lowest-level-in-two-weeks.html
The lira weakened for a second day
and headed for the lowest level in more than two weeks in
Istanbul trade.  The lira dropped 0.1 percent to 1.7967 per dollar, the
lowest level since March 23 on a closing basis.  Yields (BENCH)  on two-
year benchmark bonds dropped six basis points, or 0.06
percentage point, to 9.32 percent on April 6.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Selcuk Gokoluk in Istanbul at 
 sgokoluk@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
